# Whitelist: deny everything by default, then allow ONLY files needed for
# the Docker build context.
#
# ⚠️  Build context scope: this file lives at the repo root but each service's
# `docker compose build` uses a subdirectory as its context (./reclip, ./bot,
# ./dashboard). Docker reads .dockerignore from the context root, NOT from the
# repo root — so this file is currently DEAD CODE for the production builds.
# It serves as a defensive whitelist in case anyone later changes a build
# context to the repo root.

# --- deny all files (hidden + non-hidden) -----------------------------------
.*
*

# --- allow common tracked source/config file types -------------------------
!*.py
!*.yml
!*.yaml
!*.md
!*.sh
!*.html
!*.css
!*.js
!*.svg
!*.png
!*.jpg
!*.jpeg
!*.txt
!*.json
!*.toml
!Dockerfile
!Dockerfile.*

# --- allow all directories (so patterns above can match their contents) ----
!*/

# --- explicit denies for hidden directories the allow rules above would
# otherwise re-introduce. !*/ brings back every directory; these patterns
# (no leading !) re-deny the IDE/tooling directories that should never be
# in a build context.
.vscode/
.vscode/**
.idea/
.idea/**

# --- explicit denies (override the allow rules above for known-bad paths) ---
# Secrets, build artifacts, runtime data, IDE/OS files — none of these
# belong in a Docker image.
DESIGN.md
CLAUDE.md
docs/
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.venv/
downloads/
telegram-bot-api-data/
dashboard-data/
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache
.pytest_cache/**
*.log
*.tmp
.DS_Store
tests/
**/tests/

# --- explicitly allow tracked hidden files ---------------------------------
!.gitignore
!.dockerignore
!.env.example